Learn More DC VAULT DC Vault is the Premiere Pole Vault club in the Washington, DC Metro Region. Serving the District of Columbia, Virginia, Maryland, Delaware and Pennsylvania, DC Vault provides year-round training for beginner through elite-level athletes. Come Visit our Training Facilities The most complete training program in the region! DCV PREP PG KIDS Through a variety of partnerships, DC Vault provides training at 4 facilities in the Washington, DC metropolitan area. Each facility has been uniquely outfitted with a wide array of specialized equipment provided by the club, allowing for training targeted to athletes of all skill levels. Check out the DC Vault Home Training Facility! Previous Next Meet DC VAULT EDWARD LUTHY President Head Coach Edward Luthy - President / Head Coach Coach Luthy's experience spans over 30 years as a pole vault coach. During that time he has instructed countless athletes at all levels of competition. Having developed his own training system with roots based in Russian pole vault programs, he believes that strict adherence to step by step technical progression provides each athlete with the greatest opportunity to obtain their maximum potential and perform consistently throughout their competitive career. Primarily a self trained pole vaulter, he cleared a competitive PR of 17'1" (5.20m) before succumbing early on to an Achilles tendon injury. He competed on a full scholarship for Western Michigan University from 1999-2001, the All Army Track Team from 1993-1995 and earned varsity letters at 3 different high schools. A few athletes who have trained extensively with or are still training under Coach Luthy, and the accomplishments they have achieved during their careers include: Bill Deerring - 1996 Olympic Trials Finalist / 1989 MI State Champion Geoff Fairbanks - 2002 NCAA National Championships Finalist / 1998 MI State Champion Janice Keppler - 2012 Olympic Trials Finalist / 2007 NCAA Division I National Championships Finalist / Eastern Michigan University Record Holder Howard Booth - 2013 World Masters Champion / Masters State Record Holder in MI, OH, IL, IN Olivia Gruver - USA NCAA Division I National Record Holder / 2x NCAA Division I National Champion / 2015 MD State Champion-Record Holder Abbey Alcon - Dominican Republic National Record Holder / 2016 NACAC U21 Bronze Medalist Calvin Pitney - NCAA Division III National Champion / 2015 USATF Youth National Champion-Record Holder / 4x MD State Champion Molly Minnig - 2x Ivy League Champion / University of Pennsylvania Record Holder Robert Mercer - 2x MEAC Conference Champion / Howard University Record Holder Coaching Certifications National Pole Vault Coaches Association - Pole Vault Coaching Certification National Pole Vault Safety Certification Board - Pole Vault Safety Certification National Federation of High School Associations - Pole Vault Coaching Certification Coaching Positions Pole Vault Coach: DC Vault 2008-present Pole Vault Coach: University of Maryland 2008-2010 and 2016-present Pole Vault Coach: National Pole Vault Association 2018-present Pole Vault Adviser: Howard University 2013-2015 Pole Vault Adviser: Catholic University of America 2010-2016 Pole Vault Coach: Ann Arbor Pole Vault Club 2005-2008 Pole Vault Coach: Eastern Michigan University 2003-2008 Pole Vault Coach: Western Michigan University 2002-2003 Pole Vault Coach: Loy Norrix High School 1996-1998 Pole Vault Coach: Mitchel's Pole Vault Clinic 1996-2000 Assistant Pole Vault Coach: Sky Jumpers Pole Vault Clinics 1990-1992 Pole Vault Coach: Paw Paw High School 1990-1991 Pole Vault Coach: Lawrence High School Pole Vault Clinic 1988 Assistant Pole Vault Coach: Mitchel's Pole Vault Clinic 1988-1991 CHAD ACKERMAN Assistant Coach Chad Ackerman - Assistant Coach Coach Ackerman has over 12 years of pole vaulting experience. Growing up in Pennsylvania, he competed in the pole vault for his high school track team, claiming multiple invitational championship titles and claiming his district championship title. 
                    Later, while attending Penn State University, he was responsible for building the Penn State Pole Vault Club team from 1 participant to a total of 10 members, whom he instructed. 
                    Simultaneously Coach Ackerman worked with high school pole vaulters at McDowell. In 2018 Coach Ackerman relocated to the DC area and joined DC Vault in order to continue his own training. Soon after arriving, coach Ackerman proved himself to be an invaluable member of the organization and today assists with instruction of beginners through emerging elite athletes, as well as a wide range of administrative tasks. Certifications National Pole Vault Coaches Association - Pole Vault Coaching Certification National Pole Vault Safety Certification Board - Pole Vault Safety Certification National Federation of High School Associations - Pole Vault Coaching Certification LAUREN ROSE Administrative Assistant Lauren Rose - Administrative Assistant As the original DC Vault member, Lauren Rose has been an integral part of the organization since 2008, supporting DC Vault as a fiercely loyal athlete, an assistant coach and team administrative assistant.
                    From behind the scenes, Lauren keeps DC Vault running by organizing events, keeping track of our coaching certifications and much more. CHRIS SPIESS Assistant Coach Video Production Chris Spiess - Assistant Coach / Video Production Coach Spiess began his vaulting career with DC Vault in 2014 as a sophomore in high school. After several County and Regional Championship titles, as well as one State Championships title, he emerged as a promising collegiate vaulter for the University of Maryland and a Volunteer Coach with DC Vault. 
                    Due to Coach Spiess's extensive knowledge of the inner workings of DC Vault - having worked his way through the organizations beginner, intermediate and emerging elite programs - he has the ability to single handedly instruct and lead athletes at a variety of levels. Certifications National Pole Vault Coaches Association - Pole Vault Coaching Certification National Pole Vault Safety Certification Board - Pole Vault Safety Certification National Federation of High School Associations - Pole Vault Coaching Certification TIMOTHY SANTOSA Assistant Coach Web Developer Strength Coach Timothy Santosa - Assistant Coach / Web Developer / Strength Coach Coach Tim joined the DC Vault Level I program as a high school sophomore in 2012. Progressing quickly, he was offered a Level III training slot with the DC Vault Emerging Elite group in 2014. Despite injury, he successfully claimed 3 Regional Championship titles, 1 County Championship title and took Gold at the Maryland 4A State Championships with a height of 13'6" in 2015. Going on to attend the University of Maryland as a Computer Science major, Coach Tim continued his training in the DC Vault Emerging Elite program and began instructing Level I and II athletes in 2016. Since then, he has taken on increasingly complex coaching duties and become a core member of the DC Vault team. Additionally, Coach Tim leads the Beginner/Intermediate Strength Training program and is the current webmaster for DCVault.com Certifications National Pole Vault Coaches Association - Pole Vault Coaching Certification National Pole Vault Safety Certification Board - Pole Vault Safety Certification National Federation of High School Associations - Pole Vault Coaching Certification Training Schedule DC VAULT EVENTS Visit our events page to learn about all of our upcoming and past events. About Us - The Vault Skip to content About Us Personal Training Classes Classes Timetable Memberships Ten10 Cafe Events About Us Personal Training Classes Classes Timetable Memberships Ten10 Cafe Events JOIN NOW about us Welcome to the  vault health CLUB where fitness meets fun Your journey to your best self starts with a one-to-one session with our coaches, to kickstart your journey and keep a steady progress. From absolute beginners to professional competitors, we have you covered with tailored training and bespoke nutrition plans. With 2 free weight areas and large range of diverse equipment, The Vault gives you a 360 degree workout. If motivation is your thing our classes give you the supportive community to keep going, from yoga to high-energy ride and Circuit, catering to all levels. But wait, there’s more! It’s not just about fitness here; we organise exclusive, fun events that take us on outward-bound adventures for mind and body. Mountain hike, anyone? Like you, our friendly staff are passionate about a wide range of fitness interests, so there’s always someone ready to guide you every step of the way. Our goal is to help you unlock your potential and reach your fitness goals with a smile on your face. workout zones Personal Training Studio Women's only studio Education Studio CORE strength ZONE 2 Full free weight areas FUNCTIONAL TRAINING ZONE TRX workout area UPCOMING EVENTS VIEW MEMBERSHIPS WOMENS ZONE WOMENS ZONE We get it, gyms can be intimidating so if you want to be your best self but feel a little self conscious we offer a women’s zone and private studios. You get the results you want as you tone up and get fit in a supportive environment with the same equipment you’d find on the main gym floor. - FREE WEIGHTS - CARDIO MACHINES - CROSS TRAINER - STEPPER - SQUAT RACK - BIKE - AMT - TREADMILL - HIP THRUST MACHINE We like to think of it as a sanctuary of support and wellness. Feel Welcome, Feel Good, Feel Fitter! MEET OUR FITNESS FAMILY Like you our dynamic dream team is passionate about fitness and a balanced lifestyle. More than just trainers, we’re your personal cheerleaders, coaches and motivators, dedicated to creating the best version of you. With a unique and diverse range of skills that blend multi sporting expertise, energy, and enthusiasm, we’re here to make each fitness journey tailored to your needs. From smashing personal records to conquering new challenges together, we know that a varied approach to training brings the best results. Join us and let’s write your fitness story, where each chapter is filled with strength, determination and a whole lot of fun. Let’s unleash your potential and conquer those goals LUKE LEARN MORE OLIVIA LEARN MORE PETE LEARN MORE JAY LEARN MORE PETE LEARN MORE TOMMY LEARN MORE SEAN LEARN MORE CAITLIN LEARN MORE Emelie LEARN MORE SEAN LEARN MORE CAITLIN LEARN MORE Patrycja LEARN MORE Patrycja LEARN MORE SEAN TRAINER CAITLIN TRAINER KEEP UP TO DATE WITH THE LATEST DOWNLOAD THE APP You can easily reserve classes by downloading our app for convenient access to our booking system. As a member, you can secure your spot in classes up to 10 days in advance! Additionally, through the platform, you have the flexibility to manage your bookings, follow tailored workout plans, and engage in ongoing gym challenges. App Store Google Play MEMBERSHIPS CLASSES TIMETABLE CONTACT US Instagram Facebook Envelope Phone-alt Map-marker-alt Belgard Square West, Tallaght, Dublin 24, D24A2PX The Vault © 2025 │ PRIVACY POLICY │ BUILT BY ASHBOURNE MANAGEMENT OPENING HOURS MON - THUR - 5:30am - 10pm FRI - 5:30am - 9pm SAT - 8am - 7pm SUN - 9am - 5pm BANK HOLIDAYS - 9am - 5pm The Vault © 2025 │ PRIVACY POLICY │ BUILT BY ASHBOURNE MANAGEMENT MEET LUKE fitness philosophy Balance out your workouts, rest and listen to your body. FITNESS BACKGROUND The gym kept me focused, grounded & out of trouble growing up. It’s inspired me to help others to do the do same. I’ve worked in a boxing club & have a background in boxing & mixed martial arts. FAVOURITE FITNESS QUOTE What doesn’t challenge you, doesn’t change you. MEET OLIVIA fitness philosophy It’s never too late to start, no matter your fitness level, don’t compare yourself to others, find what works for you & enjoy it. FITNESS BACKGROUND I found a passion for health & fitness, & wanted to inspire/help others achieve their goals. My own fitness journey began years ago in Fit4Less Tallaght & I haven’t looked back. FAVOURITE FITNESS QUOTE Mindset is everything, consistency is key. MEET PETE fitness philosophy Ruthless execution of the basics will always prevail. FITNESS BACKGROUND Played lots of sports as a child like football, basketball, badminton, tennis, boxing & started in the gym at 14. I began coaching friends at20, then got qualified. I’ve been coaching professionally for over a decade now and love it! my top training tip Leave nothing to chance. Cut through all the confusion & accelerate your results by hiring a coach! favourite fitness quote The best time to plant a tree was 20 years ago, the next best time is today! MEET JAY fitness philosophy I am always here to help you achieve your goals. FITNESS BACKGROUND Always loved football, then got into the gym at 16 & haven’t looked back since. MY TOP TRAINING TIP Have goal in mind, make a plan, & work towards it. FAVOURITE FITNESS QUOTE Lightweight baby. MEET Tommy fitness philosophy Physical & mental fitness go hand in hand, so why neglect either? FITNESS BACKGROUND I’m in the industry over 7 years & have a wide range of interests & experience from Boxing to bodybuilding. I’ve used fitness as an outlet for my mental health and highly encourage others to do the same (if they aren’t already). MY TOP TRAINING TIP DO NOT compare your journey with others,  maximize your strengths & inspire others.”someone else’s”, it’s not healthy, take your time & monitor your own progress in. FAVOURITE FITNESS QUOTE Know yourself, accept your limitations, maximize your strengths & inspire others. MEET SEAN fitness philosophy It’s you VS. you. The only person you should be comparing yourself to & trying to beat, is you. 1% improvements add up. FITNESS BACKGROUND Played basketball for years, love swimming & hiking. I have a degree in science & I’m passionate about all things nutrition & fitness MY TOP TRAINING TIP Train with intention & TRACK your lifts. FAVOURITE FITNESS QUOTE The secret of change is to focus all of your energy, not on fighting the old but on building the new.
